<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" ><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.1.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><updated>2021-01-29T20:52:20+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Hermosawave Photography</title><subtitle>A series of daily landscape photographs by Daniel Sofer, over 16 years running.</subtitle><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><entry><title type="html">Togetsu Bridge・渡月橋</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210129/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Togetsu Bridge・渡月橋" /><published>2021-01-29T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2021-01-29T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/togetsu</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210129/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    A compressed, black &amp;amp; white look at the Togetsu or &lt;em&gt;Moon Crossing&lt;/em&gt; Bridge. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The current bridge dates from 1934, but there has been a bridge here for 1200 years. It has been portrayed in numerous artwork, including &lt;a href=&quot;https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e9/Unusual_Views_of_Celebrated_Bridges_in_the_Provinces-Yamashiro_Arashiyama_Togetsukyou.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;this ukiyo-e print by Hokusai&lt;/a&gt; from around 1830. 
&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    渡月橋の白黒写真。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;

    現在の橋は1934年に建てられましたが、ここには1200年前から橋があります。 &lt;a href=&quot;https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e9/Unusual_Views_of_Celebrated_Bridges_in_the_Provinces-Yamashiro_Arashiyama_Togetsukyou.jpg&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;葛飾北斎の浮世絵&lt;/a&gt;（1830年頃）など、多くの絵が橋で描かれています。

&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Togetsu Bridge" /><category term="Black and White" /><summary type="html">A compressed, black &amp;amp; white look at the Togetsu or Moon Crossing Bridge. The current bridge dates from 1934, but there has been a bridge here for 1200 years. It has been portrayed in numerous artwork, including this ukiyo-e print by Hokusai from around 1830.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2021/2101_A7R01842.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Shogen-ji Temple・松巌寺</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210128/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Shogen-ji Temple・松巌寺" /><published>2021-01-28T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2021-01-28T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/shogen-ji</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210128/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    Shogen-ji Temple, in the Tenryu-ji Temple precinct. It is usually closed to the public. &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fukurokuju&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Fukurokuju&lt;/a&gt;, one of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Seven_Lucky_Gods&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Seven Lucky Gods&lt;/a&gt;, is enshrined here.
&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
天龍寺境内の松巌寺。 一般公開されていません。 天龍寺七福神めぐりの一つ、福禄寿がここに祀られています。

&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Temples" /><category term="Tenryu-ji" /><summary type="html">Shogen-ji Temple, in the Tenryu-ji Temple precinct. It is usually closed to the public. Fukurokuju, one of the Seven Lucky Gods, is enshrined here.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2021/2101_IMG_2232.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Plum Blossoms・白梅</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210126/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Plum Blossoms・白梅" /><published>2021-01-26T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2021-01-26T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/white-plum</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210126/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    White plum blossoms along the Katsura River. A boat passes by.
&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    桂川沿いの白梅。 ボートが通り過ぎる。

&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Flowers" /><summary type="html">White plum blossoms along the Katsura River. A boat passes by.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2021/2101_A7R01805.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Katsura River・桂川</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210125/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Katsura River・桂川" /><published>2021-01-25T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2021-01-25T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/katsura</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210125/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    Crossing the Katsura River while riding on the train. In the vicinity of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Katsura_Imperial_Villa&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Katsura Imperial Villa&lt;/a&gt;.
&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    この写真は、電車に乗って桂川を渡っているときに撮ったものです。 &lt;a href=&quot;https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/桂離宮&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;桂離宮&lt;/a&gt;の近くです。

&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Katsura River" /><summary type="html">Crossing the Katsura River while riding on the train. In the vicinity of the Katsura Imperial Villa.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2021/2101_A7R01795-2.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Misty Mountains・霧が掛かった山</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210122/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Misty Mountains・霧が掛かった山" /><published>2021-01-22T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2021-01-22T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/misty-mountain</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210122/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
   Morning fog in the mountains of Arashiyama.
&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    嵐山の朝霧。

&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Fog" /><category term="Mountains" /><category term="Black and White" /><summary type="html">Morning fog in the mountains of Arashiyama.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2021/2101_A7R01744.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Scenic Garden・名勝庭園</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210121/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Scenic Garden・名勝庭園" /><published>2021-01-21T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2021-01-21T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/chishakuin-garden</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210121/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    The Edo era Scenic Garden at Chishakuin Temple. Will have to return when the rhododendrons are in bloom.
&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    智積院の江戸時代名勝園。 シャクナゲが咲いたらまた訪れたいです。

&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Gardens" /><summary type="html">The Edo era Scenic Garden at Chishakuin Temple. Will have to return when the rhododendrons are in bloom.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2021/2101_IMG_2198.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Katsura River・桂川</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210119/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Katsura River・桂川" /><published>2021-01-19T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2021-01-19T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/katsura</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210119/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    Looking southeast down the Katsura River.
    
    
&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    桂川の下流を見っている。

&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Katsura River" /><summary type="html">Looking southeast down the Katsura River.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2021/2101_A7R01722.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Laurel・アオキ</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210118/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Laurel・アオキ" /><published>2021-01-18T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2021-01-18T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/aoki</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210118/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
    A Japanese Laurel, with leaves turning, is illuminated by the morning sun.
    
    
&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    アオキは朝日に照らされています。

&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Flowers" /><summary type="html">A Japanese Laurel, with leaves turning, is illuminated by the morning sun.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2021/2101_IMG_2178.jpg" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Goeidomon Gate・御影堂門</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210116/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Goeidomon Gate・御影堂門" /><published>2021-01-16T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2021-01-16T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/honganji</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/210116/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
